# Input: schema.cedarschema
```cedar
// Nested Namespaces — Company::Identity and Company::Billing::Invoice.
//
// Exercises Cedar's multi-level namespace support and cross-namespace
// entity type references. Entity types declared in one namespace
// (Company::Identity) are used as field types on entities in another
// (Company::Billing::Invoice).
//
// The three-level namespace `Company::Billing::Invoice` is a realistic
// pattern for enterprise apps where a top-level org namespace contains
// multiple product namespaces, each of which organizes a specific
// domain of resources and actions.

namespace Company::Identity {
    entity Employee = {
        department: String,
        level: Long,
    };

    entity Team = {
        manager: Employee,
    };
}

namespace Company::Billing::Invoice {
    entity Line = {
        total: Long,
        issuer: Company::Identity::Employee,
        owningTeam: Company::Identity::Team,
    };

    // view: anyone on the team or the issuer may view a line.
    // approve: team-lead or sufficiently senior employee may approve.
    // void: senior managers only (irreversible action).
    action view, approve, void appliesTo {
        principal: [Company::Identity::Employee],
        resource: [Line],
        context: {},
    };
}
```
